      "writtenOn": "2017-01-10T15:38:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The large made-up numbers made this hard to follow.  I think it\u0027d be easier follow if you just explain mechanically what happens instead of making up probabilities.  Something like\n\nSkArenaAlloc allocates first out of an (optional) user-provided block of memory, and when that\u0027s exhausted it allocates on the heap, starting with an allocation of extra_size bytes.  If your data (plus a small overhead) fits in the user-provided block, SkArenaAlloc never uses the heap, and if it fits in extra_size bytes, it\u0027ll use the heap only once.  If you pass extra_size \u003d 0, we\u0027ll use the heap in Some Reasonable Way.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 119,
        "startChar": 46,
        "endLine": 122,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "ea922e06bf1303fb3b699e3f8c31e8ad0e687fd4",
